pose endpoints not backend-specific — DEFAULT_ENDPOINTS still show Victoria ports even for ELK backend. Known gap, not in ACs.\n\n### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — code-review (2026-03-25T03:25:00Z)\n\n- HIGH (fixed): Missing CLI validation for --observability-backend — unsafe `as` cast allows arbitrary strings\n- MEDIUM (fixed): ELK compose file resolution — 4 formatter functions resolved to Victoria compose even for ELK backend\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Wrong endpoints displayed for ELK — Victoria ports shown instead of OpenSearch ports\n- MEDIUM (fixed): resolveEndpoints() not backend-aware — always returned Victoria defaults\n- LOW (unfixed): --no-observability vs --observability-backend none have subtly different semantics\n- LOW (unfixed): formatters.ts at 605 lines — pre-existing violation, now worse\n- LOW (unfixed): docker-setup.ts at exactly 300 lines — fragile\n- Coverage gap: No integration tests for full init --observability-backend elk CLI flow\n- Architecture: buildScopedEndpoints() uses Victoria-specific URL patterns meaningless for ELK\n\n### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — verification-infra (2026-03-25T03:28:00Z)\n\n- Docker daemon unavailable despite Docker Desktop processes running. Socket exists but not responding.\n- Waited 120+ seconds across two attempts. Infra attempt 3/10 (cumulative with prior sessions).\n- Story skipped — cannot run black-box verification without Docker.\n\n### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — create-story (2026-03-25T03:32:00Z)\n\n- Observation: env.ts already over 300-line limit at 313 lines (pre-existing violation). Story guides extraction to dockerfile-generator.ts.\n- Observation: nodejs.ts at 346 lines — also over 300-line limit. Adding getVerifyDockerfileSection() will increase it further.\n- Risk: Static template deprecation — generated approach replaces them entirely. If external consumers reference templates directly, they'll break silently.\n- Ambiguity: Ubuntu 22.04 vs stack-specific base images. Architecture specifies ubuntu:22.04 but current templates use node:20-slim and rust:1.82-slim. Switching increases build time.\n\n### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — dev-story (2026-03-25T03:41:00Z)\n\n- env.ts still at 304 lines — down from 313 but still over the 300-line NFR1 limit by 4 lines. Further extraction out of scope.\n- Static templates not deleted — kept deprecated for backward compat with older installed versions. Now dead code from main build path.\n- NodejsProvider at 358 lines — exceeds 300-line NFR1. Was 346 pre-story, added 12 lines. Pre-existing tech debt.\n\n### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — verification-infra (2026-03-25T03:50:00Z)\n\n- Docker daemon not running — socket not responding. Cannot start observability stack.\n- Retry count incremented from 3 to 4. Story remains at verifying.\n- Same infrastructure issue as prior session — Docker Desktop needs to be started manually on macOS.\n\n### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — verification-infra (2026-03-25T03:50:00Z)\n\n- Docker daemon not running — same issue as 14-4. Cannot perform black-box verification.\n- Retry count corrected: 14-5 was actually at `backlog` in sprint-state.json (yaml was stale). Reset to 0.\n\n### 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget — create-story (2026-03-25T03:52:00Z)\n\n- Expanded from 2 to 10 ACs covering status ownership, time budget logic, prompt cleanup, build/test gates\n- Risk: AC6 (remove state-writing from prompts) depends on finding all prompt instructions — may miss indirect ones\n- Risk: Session budget plumbing from ralph to TS orchestrator not fully specified\n- Data inconsistency found: sprint-state.json had 14-5 as `backlog` but yaml had `verifying`. Fixed both to `verifying`.\n\n### 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget — dev-story (2026-03-25T04:00:00Z)\n\n- Architectural mismatch: run.ts spawns a single long-running ralph process. Time budget deferral logs warnings but cannot actually kill/pause the subagent mid-phase. True phase-level control would need ralph to expose phase-change events.\n- Status ownership simplification: `story-complete` event always writes `in-review`. A phase-aware mapping would be more correct but requires knowing what phase fired the event (not in the event payload).\n- All 3729 vitest tests + 307 BATS tests pass. Build succeeds.\n\n### 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget — code-review (2026-03-25T04:10:00Z)\n\n- HIGH (fixed): Time budget deferral was fire-and-forget — logged but never killed the agent process. Now calls child.kill('SIGTERM').\n- HIGH (fixed): updateStoryStatus() return value silently discarded. Now logs warnings on failure.\n- MEDIUM (fixed): shouldDeferPhase returned false for NaN input (don't defer when budget unknown). Now returns true (safe default).\n- LOW (unfixed): warn import inconsistency — warnings emitted via info() with [WARN] prefix instead of using warn() helper.\n- Coverage gap: No integration test for full deferral flow (polling -> deferral -> child.kill -> clean exit).\n- Architecture: child.kill('SIGTERM') is abrupt — no graceful shutdown protocol for subagent to save progress.\n- Architecture: 5-second polling interval means up to 5s window where phase could start before deferral.\n- All 3733 tests pass. 96.97% overall coverage. All 156 files above 80% floor.\n\n### 14-4/14-5/14-6 — verification-infra (2026-03-25T00:14:00Z)\n\n- Docker daemon not running — `docker ps` returns \"Cannot connect to the Docker daemon\". Same issue as prior sessions.\n- All three verifying stories (14-4, 14-5, 14-6) skipped. Retry counts incremented: 14-4→6, 14-5→1, 14-6→1.\n- Cannot fix Docker Desktop startup programmatically on macOS.\n\n### 14-7-fix-beads-flags-ralph-tracking-proof-docs — create-story (2026-03-25T00:14:30Z)\n\n- Story file already existed with full content and correct verification tags. No changes needed.\n\n### 14-7-fix-beads-flags-ralph-tracking-proof-docs — dev-story (2026-03-25T00:27:00Z)\n\n- AC3 spec mismatch: Story said \"flag-setting logic only triggers for npm test\" but coverage pipeline already handles Rust/Python/Node.js. No production code change needed — only added test to prove it works.\n- Fix 4 (ralph.sh) not unit-testable: bash changes not covered by vitest. BATS tests not added (not in scope).\n- `isBeadsCLIInstalled()` uses `which` — Unix-only, acceptable for target platform.\n- `get_current_task()` depends on jq — silently falls back to `unknown` if jq missing.\n\n### 14-4/14-5/14-6 — verification-infra (2026-03-25T00:30:00Z)\n\n- Docker daemon not running — `open /Applications/Docker.app` fails with error -1712 (GUI app cannot be launched from headless context).\n- All three verifying stories skipped. Retry counts incremented: 14-4→7, 14-5→2, 14-6→2.\n- Same recurring issue — Docker Desktop requires manual start on macOS.\n\n### 14-7-fix-beads-flags-ralph-tracking-proof-docs — code-review (2026-03-25T00:35:00Z)\n\n- No HIGH or MEDIUM bugs found.\n- LOW (unfixed): resolveStoryFilePath() uses .endsWith('.md') which breaks for gap-id appended descriptions. Pre-existing.\n- LOW (unfixed): readStoryFileStatus regex could match inside fenced code blocks. Unlikely in practice.\n- LOW (unfixed): isBeadsCLIInstalled() 5000ms timeout unnecessarily high but harmless.\n- Coverage: 96.97% overall, all 156 files above 80% floor.\n- No items sent back for re-development.\n\n### 15-1-ci-file-size-gate — create-story (2026-03-25T00:42:00Z)\n\n- Observation: 11 files exceed 300 lines, 15 command files exceed 100 lines despite Epic 12 being done.\n- Risk: AC2 (zero violations) not achievable without future file-split stories. Gate set to warn mode.\n- Observation: NFR5 (commands <100 lines) has 15 violators — may warrant own epic.\n\n### 15-1-ci-file-size-gate — dev-story (2026-03-25T00:46:00Z)\n\n- AC2 intentionally unmet: gate in warn mode since 11 files still exceed 300 lines. Needs future TD stories.\n- `env -u` portability: macOS `env` doesn't support `-u` flag, used `unset` in BATS tests instead.\n- No edge case test for missing `src/commands/` directory.\n\n### 15-1-ci-file-size-gate — code-review (2026-03-25T00:49:00Z)\n\n- HIGH (fixed): .tsx files excluded from gate — ink-renderer.tsx could grow past 300 undetected\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Empty SRC_DIR=\"\" scans project root instead of src/\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Trailing slash in SRC_DIR produces double-slash in annotations\n- MEDIUM (fixed): No violation counts in output summary\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Missing off-by-one boundary tests (301/101 lines)\n- LOW (unfixed): find output ordering non-deterministic across platforms\n- LOW (unfixed): 2>/dev/null on NFR5 find silently swallows all errors\n- 18 BATS tests, 325 total BATS pass, 96.97% coverage\n\n### 14-4/14-5/14-6 — verification-infra (2026-03-25T01:01:00Z)\n\n- Docker daemon not running — `open -a Docker` fails with error -1712, `docker info` returns \"Cannot connect to Docker daemon\"\n- All three verifying stories skipped. Retry counts incremented: 14-4→9, 14-5→3, 14-6→3.\n- Same recurring issue — Docker Desktop requires manual start on macOS.\n\n### 15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests — create-story (2026-03-25T01:04:00Z)\n\n- Epic says \"53 bare catch {} blocks\" but actual codebase has 134. Epic definition is stale.\n- AC2 already implemented — existing boundary test covers NFR4. Task 5 is verification-only.\n- ESLint // IGNORE: enforcement split across two tools (ESLint + vitest) — pragmatic workaround.\n- Risk: 134 catch block audit is mechanical but high-volume — incorrect categorizations could introduce silent bugs.\n- Risk: Barrel file re-exports may need modification for cross-module import violations.\n\n### 14-4/14-5/14-6 — verification-infra (2026-03-25T01:33:00Z)\n\n- Docker daemon not running — `docker ps` returns \"Cannot connect to the Docker daemon\"\n- All three verifying stories skipped. Retry counts incremented: 14-4→10 (exhausted), 14-5→4, 14-6→4.\n- Same recurring issue — Docker Desktop requires manual start on macOS.\n\n### 15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests — code-review (2026-03-25T01:37:00Z)\n\n- No HIGH or MEDIUM issues found\n- LOW (unfixed): Boundary test blind spot — cross-module imports between protected directories not fully detected\n- LOW (unfixed): 50 ESLint warnings (unused vars) — intentionally at warn level, needs future cleanup\n- LOW (unfixed): `catch(err) {}` pattern not covered by boundary test, mitigated by ESLint no-empty rule\n- 3744 tests pass, 96.97% coverage, all 156 files above 80% floor\n\n### 15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests — verification (2026-03-25T01:44:00Z)\n\n- Unit-testable verification — no Docker required\n- All 6 ACs passed with direct CLI evidence\n- Proof format required adjustment: parser needs `\\`\\`\\`bash` + `\\`\\`\\`output` pairs and `**Tier:** unit-testable` (not `**Verification tier:**`)\n- Beads sync failed (bd CLI not installed) — non-blocking\n","numLines":229,"startLine":1,"totalLines":229}}}
