{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J4ovvZw9YwzJXhMXQFr2YP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 15-1: CI File Size Gate + Fix Remaining Violations\n     2→\n     3→## Status: done\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want a CI check that fails if any `.ts` file exceeds 300 lines,\n     9→So that file size debt stops accumulating.\n    10→\n    11→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→- [x] AC1: Given CI pipeline runs, when any `.ts` file in `src/` (excluding `__tests__/`) exceeds 300 lines, then the build fails with the filename and line count <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [ ] AC2: Given all file splits from Epic 12 are complete, when CI gate is enabled, then it passes (zero violations) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→\n    18→## Technical Notes\n    19→\n    20→**Decision 12 (File Size Enforcement)** and **NFR1** (no file >300 lines excluding tests).\n    21→\n    22→### CI Gate Implementation\n    23→\n    24→Add to `.github/workflows/release.yml` (or a general CI workflow) in the `test` job:\n    25→\n    26→```bash\n    27→# File size gate — fail if any src .ts file exceeds 300 lines (excluding tests)\n    28→violations=$(find src -name '*.ts' -not -path '*__tests__*' -exec awk 'END{if(NR>300)print FILENAME\": \"NR\" lines\"}' {} \\;)\n    29→if [ -n \"$violations\" ]; then\n    30→  echo \"::error::File size violations (>300 lines):\""}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XUq8TPKb4DfRkGiqdwYoHy","session_id":"7c5953f4-1d55-4aa9-825f-60bc73601e00","uuid":"2a284465-9358-405a-928d-2dba79231d9a","timestamp":"2026-03-25T01:46:18.216Z"}
