{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XUq8TPKb4DfRkGiqdwYoHy","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The story file at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-3-template-migration-static-files.md` already exists and is complete. It has:\n\n- Story statement\n- 3 ACs with verification tags already appended\n- Detailed technical notes\n- Files to change section\n- Status: backlog\n\nThe verification tags are already present on all 3 ACs. Let me verify they're correct per the rules:\n\n- AC1: Inspecting directory contents for templates — can be done with CLI commands (ls, diff). Tagged `cli-verifiable`. Correct.\n- AC2: Checking that TS generators are replaced with `renderTemplate()` calls — can be verified with grep. Tagged `cli-verifiable`. Correct.  \n- AC3: Calling `renderTemplate()` and comparing output — can be verified by running a test script. Tagged `cli-verifiable`. Correct.\n\nThe story is already fully created. No modifications needed — the file exists with all required sections, correct verification tags, and appropriate technical detail.\n\n---\n\nStory file: `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-3-template-migration-static-files.md`\n\nThe story was already created from a prior session. It contains 3 ACs, all tagged `cli-verifiable`, detailed technical notes including the `renderTemplate()` function signature, target template directory structure, migration steps, and a comprehensive files-to-change list (18 files).\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Problems encountered:** The story file already existed at the target path. No creation was needed.\n- **Workarounds applied:** None — the existing file is well-formed and complete.\n- **Risks identified:**\n  - The story touches 18+ files across `src/templates/` and `templates/`. This is a large migration story that may exceed a single session's time budget.\n  - AC3 only tests `