{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016isbabNT5Qnyd4PMnTbMS5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 15-3: Template Migration -- All Templates to Static Files\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want all templates in `templates/` as static files (not generated in TypeScript),\n     9→So that there's one template system.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `templates/dockerfiles/`, `templates/prompts/`, `templates/docs/` directories, when inspected, then they contain all Dockerfile templates, prompt templates, and doc templates that were previously in `src/templates/*.ts` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given `src/templates/` TypeScript generators, when migration completes, then they're replaced with `renderTemplate()` calls reading from `templates/` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC3: Given `renderTemplate('templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.nodejs', { TARBALL: 'package.tgz' })`, when called, then it returns the same Dockerfile content as the current `nodejsTemplate()` function <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→\n    17→## Technical Notes\n    18→\n    19→**Decision 9 (Template Unification).** Two parallel template systems -> one.\n    20→\n    21→### Target Template Structure (from architecture-v3.md)\n    22→\n    23→```\n    24→templates/\n    25→  dockerfiles/\n    26→    Dockerfile.nodejs           # Was nodejsTemplate() in src/templates/*.ts\n    27→    Dockerfile.python\n    28→    Dockerfile.rust\n    29→    Dockerfile.generic\n    30→    Dockerfile.verify           # Node.js verification"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7c5953f4-1d55-4aa9-825f-60bc73601e00","uuid":"7f524990-ec2d-4d0d-b924-be0be2650e27","timestamp":"2026-03-25T01:46:58.220Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-3-template-migration-static-files.md","content":"# Story 15-3: Template Migration -- All Templates to Static Files\n\n## Status: backlog\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer,\nI want all templates in `templates/` as static files (not generated in TypeScript),\nSo that there's one template system.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC1: Given `templates/dockerfiles/`, `templates/prompts/`, `templates/docs/` directories, when inspected, then they contain all Dockerfile templates, prompt templates, and doc templates that were previously in `src/templates/*.ts` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC2: Given `src/templates/` TypeScript generators, when migration completes, then they're replaced with `renderTemplate()` calls reading from `templates/` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC3: Given `renderTemplate('templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.nodejs', { TARBALL: 'package.tgz' })`, when called, then it returns the same Dockerfile content as the current `nodejsTemplate()` function <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n## Technical Notes\n\n**Decision 9 (Template Unification).** Two parallel template systems -> one.\n\n### Target Template Structure (from architecture-v3.md)\n\n```\ntemplates/\n  dockerfiles/\n    Dockerfile.nodejs           # Was nodejsTemplate() in src/templates/*.ts\n    Dockerfile.python\n    Dockerfile.rust\n    Dockerfile.generic\n    Dockerfile.verify           # Node.js verification","numLines":30,"startLine":1,"totalLines":119}}}
