{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FKUuscgQWEuJhdYvxVhcxD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * BMAD workflow patch templates.\n     3→ * Reads patch content from `patches/{role}/{name}.md` files at runtime.\n     4→ * Falls back to inline defaults if files are not found (e.g., in npm package).\n     5→ *\n     6→ * Architecture Decision 6: Templates as files, not hardcoded strings.\n     7→ * This allows patches to be updated without rebuilding — learnings from\n     8→ * verification failures, agent misbehavior, and architectural changes\n     9→ * are captured in the patch files and applied on next init.\n    10→ *\n    11→ * Directory layout (FR35):\n    12→ *   patches/{dev,review,verify,sprint,retro}/*.md\n    13→ */\n    14→\n    15→import { readFileSync, existsSync } from 'node:fs';\n    16→import { join, dirname } from 'node:path';\n    17→import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\n    18→\n    19→const __dirname = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\n    20→\n    21→/**\n    22→ * Reads a patch file from the patches/{role}/ directory.\n    23→ * Resolves relative to package root (works for both dev and npm install).\n    24→ *\n    25→ * @param role - The role subdirectory (dev, review, verify, sprint, retro)\n    26→ * @param name - The patch file name (without .md extension)\n    27→ */\n    28→function readPatchFile(role: string, name: string): string | null {\n    29→  const patchPath = join(__dirname, '..', '..', 'patches', role, `${name}.md`);\n    30→  try {\n    31→    if (existsSync(patchPath)) {\n    32→      return readFileSync(patchPath, 'utf-8').trim();\n    33→    }\n    34→  } catch {\n    35→    // IGNORE: patch file may have disappeared between check and read\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  return null;\n    39→}\n    40→\n    41→export function storyVerificationPatch(): string {\n    42→  return readPatchFile('verify', 'story-verification') ?? `## Verification Requirements\n    43→\n    44→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/<story-key>-proof.md)\n    45→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n    46→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n    47→\n    48→## Documentation Requirements\n    49→\n    50→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n    51→- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/<story-key>.md\n    52→\n    53→## Testing Requirements\n    54→\n    55→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n    56→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%`;\n    57→}\n    58→\n    59→export function devEnforcementPatch(): string {\n    60→  return readPatchFile('dev', 'enforcement') ?? `## Codeharness Enforcement\n    61→\n    62→### Observability Check\n    63→- [ ] Query VictoriaLogs after test runs to verify telemetry flows\n    64→\n    65→### Documentation Update\n    66→- [ ] AGENTS.md updated for all changed modules\n    67→\n    68→### Test Enforcement\n    69→- [ ] All tests pass\n    70→- [ ] Coverage gate: 100% of new/changed code`;\n    71→}\n    72→\n    73→export function reviewEnforcementPatch(): string {\n    74→  return readPatchFile('review', 'enforcement') ?? `## Codeharness Review Gates\n    75→\n    76→### Verification\n    77→- [ ] Proof document exists and passes codeharness verify\n    78→- [ ] All acceptance criteria have evidence in proof document\n    79→\n    80→### Coverage\n    81→- [ ] No coverage regression in changed files`;\n    82→}\n    83→\n    84→export function retroEnforcementPatch(): string {\n    85→  return readPatchFile('retro', 'enforcement') ?? `## Codeharness Quality Metrics\n    86→\n    87→### Verification Effectiveness\n    88→- [ ] How many ACs were caught by verification vs manual review?\n    89→- [ ] Were there any false positives in proofs?\n    90→\n    91→### Test Quality\n    92→- [ ] Coverage trend (improving, stable, declining)`;\n    93→}\n    94→\n    95→export function sprintBeadsPatch(): string {\n    96→  return readPatchFile('sprint', 'planning') ?? `## Codeharness Sprint Planning\n    97→\n    98→- [ ] Review unresolved retrospective action items\n    99→- [ ] Import from all backlog sources before triage\n   100→- [ ] Verify story ACs are testable via CLI + Docker`;\n   101→}\n   102→\n   103→export function sprintPlanningRetroPatch(): string {\n   104→  // Merged into sprint-planning patch — no longer separate\n   105→  return sprintBeadsPatch();\n   106→}\n   107→\n   108→/**\n   109→ * Maps patch names to their template functions.\n   110→ */\n   111→export const PATCH_TEMPLATES: Record<string, () => string> = {\n   112→  'story-verification': storyVerificationPatch,\n   113→  'dev-enforcement': devEnforcementPatch,\n   114→  'review-enforcement': reviewEnforcementPatch,\n   115→  'retro-enforcement': retroEnforcementPatch,\n   116→  'sprint-beads': sprintBeadsPatch,\n   117→  'sprint-retro': sprintPlanningRetroPatch,\n   118→};\n   119→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01ARb5KJHwvTVWjSi4hskh96","session_id":"7c5953f4-1d55-4aa9-825f-60bc73601e00","uuid":"1499c4e6-45f1-4f30-8bbb-390785e9f834","timestamp":"2026-03-25T01:50:01.842Z"}
