{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JN82CLo3LPhN4k27JRUFLL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Ralph prompt template — generates the prompt that instructs each\n     3→ * Claude Code iteration to run /harness-run for sprint execution.\n     4→ */\n     5→\n     6→export interface RalphPromptConfig {\n     7→  projectDir: string;\n     8→  sprintStatusPath: string;\n     9→  retryCount?: number;\n    10→  currentStoryKey?: string;\n    11→  flaggedStories?: string[];\n    12→}\n    13→\n    14→const PROMPT_TEMPLATE = `You are an autonomous coding agent executing a sprint for the codeharness project.\n    15→\n    16→## Your Mission\n    17→\n    18→Run the \\`/harness-run\\` command to execute the next story in the sprint.\n    19→\n    20→## Instructions\n    21→\n    22→1. **Run \\`/harness-run\\`** — this is the sprint execution skill that:\n    23→   - Reads sprint-status.yaml at \\`{{sprintStatusPath}}\\` to find the next story\n    24→   - Picks the first story with status NOT \\`done\\` (handles \\`backlog\\`, \\`ready-for-dev\\`, \\`in-progress\\`, \\`review\\`, and \\`verified\\`)\n    25→   - Executes the appropriate BMAD workflow for the story's current status\n    26→\n    27→2. **Follow all BMAD workflows** — the /harness-run skill handles this, but if prompted:\n    28→   - Use \\`/bmad-dev-story\\` for implementation\n    29→   - Use code-review workflow for quality checks\n    30→   - Ensure tests pass and coverage meets targets\n    31→\n    32→3. **Do not skip verification** — every story must pass verification gates\n    33→   (tests, coverage, showboat proof) before being marked done.\n    34→\n    35→## Verification Gates\n    36→\n    37→After completing a story, run \\`codeharness verify --story <id>\\` to verify.\n    38→If verification fails, fix the issues and re-verify. The story is not done\n    39→until verification passes.\n    40→\n    41→## Project Context\n    42→\n    43→- **Project directory:** \\`{{projectDir}}\\`\n    44→- **Sprint status:** \\`{{sprintStatusPath}}\\`\n    45→\n    46→## Important\n    47→\n    48→- Do NOT implement your own task-picking logic. Let /harness-run handle it.\n    49→- Do NOT write to sprint-state.json or sprint-status.yaml. The orchestrator owns all status writes.\n    50→- Focus on one story per session. Ralph will spawn a new session for the next story.\n    51→`;\n    52→\n    53→/**\n    54→ * Generates the prompt content for a Ralph iteration.\n    55→ * Interpolates project-specific paths into the template.\n    56→ * Optionally includes retry context and flagged story information.\n    57→ */\n    58→export function generateRalphPrompt(config: RalphPromptConfig): string {\n    59→  let prompt = PROMPT_TEMPLATE\n    60→    .replace(/\\{\\{projectDir\\}\\}/g, config.projectDir)\n    61→    .replace(/\\{\\{sprintStatusPath\\}\\}/g, config.sprintStatusPath);\n    62→\n    63→  // Add retry context if retrying a story\n    64→  if (config.retryCount && config.retryCount > 0 && config.currentStoryKey) {\n    65→    prompt += `\\n## Retry Context\\n\\n`;\n    66→    prompt += `This is retry attempt **${config.retryCount}** for story \\`${config.currentStoryKey}\\`. `;\n    67→    prompt += `Previous attempts did not complete verification. Focus on fixing the remaining issues.\\n`;\n    68→  }\n    69→\n    70→  // Add flagged stories if any\n    71→  if (config.flaggedStories && config.flaggedStories.length > 0) {\n    72→    prompt += `\\n## Flagged Stories (Skip These)\\n\\n`;\n    73→    prompt += `The following stories have exceeded the retry limit and should be skipped:\\n`;\n    74→    for (const story of config.flaggedStories) {\n    75→      prompt += `- \\`${story}\\`\\n`;\n    76→    }\n    77→  }\n    78→\n    79→  return prompt;\n    80→}\n    81→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01ARb5KJHwvTVWjSi4hskh96","session_id":"7c5953f4-1d55-4aa9-825f-60bc73601e00","uuid":"5a21cebd-0069-4f00-85c9-d67edca5ba77","timestamp":"2026-03-25T01:50:28.427Z"}
