{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ARb5KJHwvTVWjSi4hskh96","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here is a summary of what was implemented.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Summary\n\n### Story 15-3: Template Migration — All Templates to Static Files\n\n**What was done:**\n\n1. **Added `renderTemplateFile()` to `src/lib/templates.ts`** — Reads a template file relative to the package root and interpolates `{{VAR}}` placeholders. Also added `getPackageRoot()` helper.\n\n2. **Created static template files:**\n   - `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.nodejs` — Node.js Dockerfile\n   - `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.python` — Python Dockerfile\n   - `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.rust` — Rust multi-stage Dockerfile\n   - `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.generic` — Generic Dockerfile\n   - `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.multi-stage.tmpl` — Multi-stage with `{{BUILD_STAGES}}` and `{{COPY_DIRECTIVES}}` placeholders\n   - `templates/compose/victoria.yml` — Victoria shared stack compose\n   - `templates/compose/collector-only.yml` — Collector-only compose\n   - `templates/compose/otel-collector-base.yaml` — OTel collector base config\n   - `templates/compose/otel-collector-remote.yaml` — OTel collector remote config with `{{LOGS_URL}}`, `{{METRICS_URL}}`, `{{TRACES_URL}}`\n   - `templates/prompts/ralph-prompt.md` — Ralph prompt template with `{{projectDir}}` and `{{sprintStatusPath}}`\n   - `templates/docs/readme.md.tmpl` — README template with `{{PROJECT_NAME}}`, `{{INSTALL_COMMAND}}`, `{{CLI_HELP_OUTPUT}}`\n\n3. **Replaced TypeScript inline templates with `renderTemplateFile()` calls:**\n   - `src/templates/docker-compose.ts`\n   - `src/templates/otel-config.ts`\n   - `src/templates/readme.ts`\n   - `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts`\n   - `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts`\n   - `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts`, `python.ts`, `rust.ts` (their `getDockerfileTemplate()` methods)\n\n4. **Updated test mocks** in three test files that mock `../../../lib/templates.js` to also provide `renderTemplateFile`:\n   - `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts`\n   - `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts`\n   - `src/modules/infra/__tests__/index.test.ts`\n\n5. **Wrote 31 new migration tests** in `src/templates/__tests__/template-migration.test.ts` verifying:\n   - `renderTemplate()` and `renderTemplateFile()` behavior\n   - All static Dockerfile templates match old inline content\n   - Compose templates match old inline content\n   - OTel config templates match old inline content\n   - Ralph prompt and README templates work correctly\n   - Template directory structure contains all expected files (AC1)\n   - TypeScript generators delegate to `renderTemplateFile()` (AC2)\n\n6. **Not migrated (by design):**\n   - `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` — Complex TypeScript logic (conditionals, config-driven endpoint injection, project type guidance). Cannot be represented as simple `{{VAR}}` templates.\n   - `src/templates/showboat-template.ts` — Complex TypeScript logic (loops over ACs, conditional screenshots section). Cannot be represented as simple `{{VAR}}` templates.\n   - `src/templates/bmad-patches.ts` — Already reads from files (`patches/{role}/*.md`). Already migrated in a prior story.\n\n**Test results:** 3775/3775 tests pass. Build succeeds.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Test mock fragility**: Three test files (`dockerfile-template.test.ts`, `init-project.test.ts`, `index.test.ts`) mock `node:fs` globally, which breaks any module transitively importing `readFileSync` via `renderTemplateFile`. Fixed by providing `renderTemplateFile` in the mock via `vi.importActual`. This is a recurring pattern -- any future module that uses `renderTemplateFile` will break tests that mock `node:fs` globally without providing `renderTemplateFile`. Consider a project-wide convention for this.\n- **verify-prompt.ts and showboat-template.ts not migrated**: These templates have complex TypeScript logic (conditionals, loops, computed values) that cannot be expressed as `{{VAR}}` interpolation. The story's target structure lists `templates/prompts/verify-prompt.md` and `templates/prompts/showboat-template.md` but migrating them would require either a real template engine or significant refactoring of the callers. Left as TypeScript generators for now.\n- **Dual template content for Dockerfiles**: The stack providers (`nodejs.ts`, `python.ts`, `rust.ts`) and `dockerfile-template.ts` both had identical Dockerfile content inline. Both now delegate to the same static files, eliminating the duplication."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a12afc2b48f7fa5bb (use SendMessage with to: 'a12afc2b48f7fa5bb' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 117072\ntool_uses: 110\nduration_ms: 771621</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7c5953f4-1d55-4aa9-825f-60bc73601e00","uuid":"72eb8091-1429-47ba-b890-51d686bc5fe8","timestamp":"2026-03-25T02:02:31.048Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-3-template-migration-static-files.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that felt wrong, TODOs left behind)\n- Code quality concerns (areas that need refactoring, edge cases not handled, tech debt added)\n- Observations (unexpected complexity, architectural mismatches, dependency issues)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"a12afc2b48f7fa5bb","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here is a summary of what was implemented.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Summary\n\n### Story 15-3: Template Migration — All Templates to Static Files\n\n**What was done:**\n\n1. **Added `renderTemplateFile()` to `src/lib/templates.ts`** — Reads a template file relative to the package root and interpolates `{{VAR}}` placeholders. Also added `getPackageRoot()` helper.\n\n2. **Created static template files:**\n   - `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.nodejs` — Node.js Dockerfile\n   - `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.python` — Python Dockerfile\n   - `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.rust` — Rust multi-stage Dockerfile\n   - `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.generic` — Generic Dockerfile\n   - `templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.multi-stage.tmpl` — Multi-stage with `{{BUILD_STAGES}}` and `{{COPY_DIRECTIVES}}` placeholders\n   - `templates/compose/victoria.yml` — Victoria shared stack compose\n   - `templates/compose/collector-only.yml` — Collector-only compose\n   - `templates/compose/otel-collector-base.yaml` — OTel collector base config\n   - `templates/compose/otel-collector-remote.yaml` — OTel collector remote config with `{{LOGS_URL}}`, `{{METRICS_URL}}`, `{{TRACES_URL}}`\n   - `templates/prompts/ralph-prompt.md` — Ralph prompt template with `{{projectDir}}` and `{{sprintStatusPath}}`\n   - `templates/docs/readme.md.tmpl` — README template with `{{PROJECT_NAME}}`, `{{INSTALL_COMMAND}}`, `{{CLI_HELP_OUTPUT}}`\n\n3. **Replaced TypeScript inline templates with `renderTemplateFile()` calls:**\n   - `src/templates/docker-compose.ts`\n   - `src/templates/otel-config.ts`\n   - `src/templates/readme.ts`\n   - `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts`\n   - `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts`\n   - `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts`, `python.ts`, `rust.ts` (their `getDockerfileTemplate()` methods)\n\n4. **Updated test mocks** in three test files that mock `../../../lib/templates.js` to also provide `renderTemplateFile`:\n   - `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts`\n   - `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts`\n   - `src/modules/infra/__tests__/index.test.ts`\n\n5. **Wrote 31 new migration tests** in `src/templates/__tests__/template-migration.test.ts` verifying:\n   - `renderTemplate()` and `renderTemplateFile()` behavior\n   - All static Dockerfile templates match old inline content\n   - Compose templates match old inline content\n   - OTel config templates match old inline content\n   - Ralph prompt and README templates work correctly\n   - Template directory structure contains all expected files (AC1)\n   - TypeScript generators delegate to `renderTemplateFile()` (AC2)\n\n6. **Not migrated (by design):**\n   - `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` — Complex TypeScript logic (conditionals, config-driven endpoint injection, project type guidance). Cannot be represented as simple `{{VAR}}` templates.\n   - `src/templates/showboat-template.ts` — Complex TypeScript logic (loops over ACs, conditional screenshots section). Cannot be represented as simple `{{VAR}}` templates.\n   - `src/templates/bmad-patches.ts` — Already reads from files (`patches/{role}/*.md`). Already migrated in a prior story.\n\n**Test results:** 3775/3775 tests pass. Build succeeds.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Test mock fragility**: Three test files (`dockerfile-template.test.ts`, `init-project.test.ts`, `index.test.ts`) mock `node:fs` globally, which breaks any module transitively importing `readFileSync` via `renderTemplateFile`. Fixed by providing `renderTemplateFile` in the mock via `vi.importActual`. This is a recurring pattern -- any future module that uses `renderTemplateFile` will break tests that mock `node:fs` globally without providing `renderTemplateFile`. Consider a project-wide convention for this.\n- **verify-prompt.ts and showboat-template.ts not migrated**: These templates have complex TypeScript logic (conditionals, loops, computed values) that cannot be expressed as `{{VAR}}` interpolation. The story's target structure lists `templates/prompts/verify-prompt.md` and `templates/prompts/showboat-template.md` but migrating them would require either a real template engine or significant refactoring of the callers. Left as TypeScript generators for now.\n- **Dual template content for Dockerfiles**: The stack providers (`nodejs.ts`, `python.ts`, `rust.ts`) and `dockerfile-template.ts` both had identical Dockerfile content inline. Both now delegate to the same static files, eliminating the duplication."}],"totalDurationMs":771621,"totalTokens":117072,"totalToolUseCount":110,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":317,"cache_read_input_tokens":115518,"output_tokens":1236,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":317},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
